%kSubBackGr 'calculates the approximate background intensity and subtracts it '
% This MatLab function was automatically generated by a converter (KhorosToMatLab) from the Khoros SubBackGr.pane file
%
% Parameters: 
% Double: p 'Percentage', default: 20: 'percentage (0..100) of pixels-clipping to calculate mean from'
% Toggle: histo 'use Histogram', default: 0: 'The background estimation is based on the histogram, if selected'
% Integer: bins 'Bins', default: 256: 'number of bins for histogram'
% Integer: ub 'Counting', default: 4: 'number of bins +/- next to maximum that count'
% Double: scanhp 'Fraction', default: 0.3: 'defines the fraction of the histogram that is scanned for a maximum (starting from minimum intensity)'
% Toggle: s 'use Pixelsorting', default: 0: 'algorithm sorts pixels and takes simply the first few "Percent". '
% Double: f 'Factor', default: 1: 'factor to apply to background before subtraction'
% Integer: n 'Iterations', default: 1: 'iterations to perform doing mean = mean of pixels below percentage of mean.'
% InputFile: i 'Input ', required: 'First Input data object'
% OutputFile: o 'Output', required: 'Resulting output data object'
% OutputFile: oh 'Histogram', optional: 'Resulting Histogram (with Histo method). HISTOGRAM starts allways at minimum pixel and stops at maximum !!'
%
% Example: [o, oh] = kSubBackGr(i, {'p',20;'histo',0;'bins',256;'ub',4;'scanhp',0.3;'s',0;'f',1;'n',1;'i','';'o','';'oh',''})
%
% Khoros helpfile follows below:
%
%  PROGRAM
% SubBackGr - calculates the approximate background intensity and subtracts it
%
%  DESCRIPTION
%
%  
